get.description:
Package configuration decides what kind of information is returned.
GET /apiv1/personinformation?SSN=194103222222

The endpoint can reply with the following error messages:

{
    "type": "InvalidParameters",
    "message": "SSN or Id must be supplied in the query."
}

{
    "type": "InvalidParameters",
    "message": "SSN or Id must not be supplied at the same time in query."
}

{
    "type": "InvalidParameters",
    "message": "SSN must be 12 digits long and in format yyyymmddnnnc."
}

{
    "type": "InvalidParameters",
    "message": "Id must be between 10 and 20 characters long."
}

{
    "type": "InvalidParameters",
    "message": "ZipCode must be 5 digits long."
}

{
    "responseCode": "NotFound",
    "responseMessage": "Supplied Id did not match a person"
}

{
    "responseCode": "NotFound",
    "responseMessage": "Supplied SSN did not match a person"
}

{
    "responseCode": "Ok",
    "responseMessage": "Person did not match ZipCode"
}

{
    "responseCode": "FraudFlag",
    "responseMessage": "The person has lost his/her identity credentials"
}

{
    "responseCode": "NotFound",
    "responseMessage": "Not found"
}

{
    "responseCode": "FraudFlag",
    "responseMessage": "Has fraud protection flag"
}

{
    "responseCode": "Deceased",
    "responseMessage": "Deceased for more than 6 months"
}

{
    "responseCode": "DeRegistered",
    "responseMessage": ""
}

{
    "responseCode": "Ok",
    "responseMessage": "Protected identity"
}

{
    "responseCode": "Ok",
    "responseMessage": "Emigrated or no information"
}

For an example response, use SSN 191010101010.

